  issn = {1669-3582},
  urldate = {2026-05-19},
  abstract = {Discover this 2015 paper in Revista Electr\'onica de Psicolog\'ia Pol\'itica by Rom\'an Brugnoli, Jos\'e Antonio; and, Osorio Gonnet, Cecilia focusing on: CHILE; CHILEAN politics \& government; SOLIDARITY; NEOLIBERALISM; SOCIAL responsibility; POLICY sciences; COALITION governments; SOCIAL policy Abstract: The article analyses the use of the notion of solidarity on the policy making process of public social policies during the governments of the political coalition Concertaci\'on de Partidos por la Democracia (1990-2010) in Chile. The analysis was based o a critical discourse analysis of a strategic corpus composed of twenty social public policy documents, corresponding to the phases of design, legislation and implementation. A set of phenomena which contribute to a discursive strategy -- seeking to install a relocation of social responsibility from the state to the individuals- is identify. Aspects related to the frequency and distribution of the notion of solidarity, their local contexts theming, grammar usage and the use of a lexicon style, are described. In conclusion, the use of the notion of solidarity gave a solidarity image to social policies structured under neoliberal principles, and built a moral support for those initiatives.},
